text: Xenorhabdus miraniensis is a bacterium from the genus of Xenorhabdus which has been isolated from a Steinernema species from Mirani in Australia.Deutsche Sammlung von Mikroorganismen und Zellkulturen UniProt Xenorhabdus miraniensis produces the antibiotics xenocoumacin and xenorhabdin. == References == == Further reading == * ==External links== *Type strain of Xenorhabdus miraniensis at BacDive - the Bacterial Diversity Metadatabase Category:Bacteria described in 2006
title: Xenorhabdus miraniensis
